## Infection Trends EDA — Nigeria Public Health Analysis

Exploratory data analysis on 2 years of monthly infection data 
across 5 Nigerian states, simulating a real-world NCDC surveillance dataset.

**Tools:** Python, pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn  
**Skills demonstrated:** EDA, statistical testing, correlation analysis, 
time series visualisation, epidemiological interpretation

**Dataset:** 120 rows × 10 columns — infection counts, mortality, 
recovery, rainfall, and temperature across Lagos, Abuja, Kano, Rivers, and Oyo

**Key findings:**
- Kano and Lagos recorded the highest average infection counts
- No significant correlation between rainfall and infection count 
  (Spearman r=-0.08, p=0.41)
- Lagos showed significantly higher mortality rates than Kano 
  (t=2.98, p=0.005), suggesting disparities in healthcare access
- March 2023 recorded the highest monthly infection count across all states

**Recommendation:**
Targeted public health campaigns focusing on hygiene and sanitation 
in high-density northern states, alongside investment in Lagos healthcare 
infrastructure to reduce case fatality rates.
